DEPENDENCIES
 bash >=4.0
 coreutils
 findutils
 fuse3
 fuse-overlayfs
 glib2 (optional for suspend-sync support via gdbus)
 kmod
 rsync
 systemd

WARNING
To avoid data loss, it is HIGHLY recommended that users stop any running
versions of this software before install updates. Internal changes are
always possible from one release to another.

BUILDING
 Setup via make.

 $ make

Running `make install` as root will distribute the files to the filesystem.

 # make install

Note that it is not required in many cases, but on occasion, internals are
changed in the psd code which makes stopping any active psd session BEFORE
the make install setup a good idea.

USERS OF ATOMIC/IMMUTABLE SYSTEMS (Bazzite, Fedora Silverblue, etc.)
On atomic systems, /usr is read-only. Install to your user home instead:

 $ make
 $ make user-install

This will install everything under ~/.local/ and systemd user units under
~/.config/systemd/user/. After installation:

 $ systemctl --user daemon-reload
 $ systemctl --user enable --now psd.service

To uninstall:

 $ make user-uninstall

USE A DISTRO PROVIDED PACKAGE
 See the project homepage for an updated list of provided packages:
 https://github.com/koloved/profile-sync-daemon-bazzite
